### expected behaviour
mac os x sync client 1.2.5 is running.
on the mac client a folder "lã¶sung" is created.
the folder is visible in the web interface.
the folder is created in the owncloud/data/... folder as well.

### actual behaviour
the folder is shown double in the web interface.
the folder is not created on the server beneath owncloud/data/...  or maybe deleted.
if i click on one of the folders "lã¶sung" in the web interface to change to the directory the web interface goes back to the root folder. then i click the folder "clientsync" in the web interface and only one folder "lã¶sung" is visible then.

### steps to reproduce
1. start os x sync client 1.2.5
2. open local owncloud folder
3. create a folder "lã¶sung" in the local owncloud folder
